Data-Context

Data-Context provides a way for configuration files to be stored hireachly
in file system paths. It also allows for the content of those configuration
files to be changed dynamically at runtime.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Build.PL
    ./Build
    ./Build test
    ./Build install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Data::Context

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Data-Context

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Data-Context

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Data-Context

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Data-Context/

    Source Code
        git://github.com/ivanwills/Data-Context.git

